treams for non-empty ones. I want to add a test for Java serialization with public `writeObject/readObject` methods. The current setup lacks imports and needs editing. I also need to cover the case where I update existing attributes, which could involve more complexities related to deserialization. It’s important that native ObjectInputStream functions as expected while keeping my approach flexible. I'll work on those write/read helpers.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Clarifying call site deduplication**\\n\\nI'm evaluating how to handle deduplication for active uncovered call sites using frame and API, and I realize that one should be sufficient. For the empty path, there might be two calls at the same call site, which adds a layer of complexity. While the static call sites exist at bytecode offsets, they only report the frame method without specifying the line, so everything has been deduplicated by frame. Alright, it's time to make those edits!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_7Zhrv801oPq7ZPJYY61HlZR6|fc_031edc299d45794f0169fbf857de5c819097ecd7e6f2611b07", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.bouncycastle/bcprov-jdk18on/1.77/src/test/java/org_bouncycastle/bcprov_jdk18on/PKCS12BagAttributeCarrierImplTest.java", "edits": [{"oldText": "import java.io.IOException;\nimport java.io.ObjectInputStream;\nimport java.io.ObjectOutputStream;\n", "newText": "import java.io.ByteArrayInputStream;\nimport java.io.ByteArrayOutputStream;\nimport java.io.IOException;\nimport java.io.ObjectInputStream;\nimport java.io.ObjectOutputStream;\n"}, {"oldText": "        RecordingObjectOutputStream outputStream = new RecordingObjectOutputStream();\n        original.writeObject(outputStream);\n\n        assertThat(outputStream.writtenObjects()).hasSize(1);\n        assertThat(outputStream.writtenObjects().get(0)).isInstanceOf(byte[].class);\n\n        PKCS12BagAttributeCarrierImpl restored = new PKCS12BagAttributeCarrierImpl();\n        restored.readObject